\r\nvalue=\\\"keithstroyde@hotmail.co.uk\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"Email\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n    Keith Stroyde\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n   </p>\r\n  </p>\r\n </p>\r\n','LEFT','2012-03-22'),(36,'MENU_ITEM',700,200,'NO','Green Guide','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n Ways to be a Good Earth Steward\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Being aware of ethical and environmental issues does not imply\r\n a lack of self interest. Saving Money and protecting the environment\r\n are not mutually exclusive positions.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Daily praise God for the world he has made.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n * \r\n </span>\r\n Use long life low energy light bulbs.\r\n<li>\r\n Recycle, repair and reuse.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n * \r\n </span>\r\n Don\\\'t leave TVs, CD players, computers etc on standby.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Stop using throwaway plastic bags. Invest in long life carrier bags.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n * \r\n </span>\r\n Have a well insulated hot water tank.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Only use \\\"grey water\\\" (dish water or bath water) for watering garden plants\r\n <br />\r\n (\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n *\r\n </span>\r\n with a water meter).\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Reduce the amount of water flushed down the toilet. Don\\\'t laugh - placing\r\n a brick in a cistern wrapped in a sealed carrier bag makes a difference.\r\n <br />\r\n (\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n *\r\n </span>\r\n with a water meter).\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Recycle your old Inkjet and Laser Toner Cartidges.\r\n <br />\r\n Christian Aid receive £1.00 for each reusable cartridge.\r\n <br />\r\n if you have any reusable Cartridges or Laser Cartridges please\r\n Contact Gloria Burrows\r\n    <a href=\\\"javascript:mailPopUp(\\\'Gloria.Burrows@ChristChurchLye.org.uk\\\')\\\">\r\n     Email\r\n    </a>\r\n\r\n <br />\r\n Hewlett Packard\r\n <br />\r\n Lexmard\r\n <br />\r\n Dell\r\n <br />\r\n Canon\r\n BC02/05/BX2/BX3\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Obsolete PCs, Printers and other hardware may be diverted to charities.\r\n <br />\r\n Contact \r\n <a href=\\\"javascript:mailPopUp(\\\'Webmaster@ChristChurchLye.org.uk\\\')\\\">\r\n Webmaster\r\n </a>\r\n for further details.\r\n\r\n</li\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n Think before flying. If you do fly, consider offsetting the CO2 produced \r\n by planting trees.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n * \r\n </span>\r\n Next time you make a major purchase of electrical goods look at the energy\r\n consumption of each model.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n *\r\n </span>\r\n If it is a short journey - walk.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n <span id=\\\"highlightred\\\">\r\n * \r\n </span>\r\n Saves money, always a consideration.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA water meter is well worth checking out. After having a water meter fitted my water bill dropped from an annual cost  of £272 to approximately £65. A saving of over £200. Check out the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.stwater.co.uk/server.php?show=nav.001001002\\\">Severn Trent Website</a>\r\nand user their website calculator to find out if moving to a water meter will save you money.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWith Energy costs rising faster than the rate of inflation some Electricity and Gas suppliers are significantly cheaper than others. Many websites offer comparative checks on energy suppliers. There are significant savings to be made, particularly if, like most people in this area, you are still using nPower the child of the old MEB.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTry these websites for price comparison checks.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.energyhelpline.com/energy/rg_home.aspx\\\">http://www.energyhelpline.com/energy/rg_home.aspx</a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.simplyswitch.com/switch-fuels.html\\\">http://www.simplyswitch.com/switch-fuels.html</a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.uswitch.com/LandingPages/energy-v3.lp\\\">http://www.uswitch.com/LandingPages/energy-v3.lp</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.greenpeace.org.uk/\\\">Greenpeace</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2007-08-11'),(28,'MENU_ITEM',450,900,'NO','Parochial Church Council','','<br/>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nParochial Church Council\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe \r\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parochial_church_council\">\r\nParochial Church Council\r\n</a>\r\n(PCC) meets on the third Monday of the month to pray, discuss, plan and have oversight for the church building.  \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"office@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n</p>','RIGHT','2009-09-21'),(29,'MENU_ITEM',700,100,'NO','Wildlife Watch','','<br />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n <a href=\\\"http://www.greenpeace.org.uk/\\\">Greenpeace</a>\r\n <BR />\r\n <a href=\\\"http://www.rspb.org.uk/\\\">RSPB</a>\r\n <br />\r\n <a href=\\\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Oddie\\\">Bill Oddie</a>\r\n <br />\r\n <a href=\\\"http://www.rspca.org.uk/\\\">RSPCA</a>\r\n <br />\r\n <a href=\\\"http://www.pdsa.org.uk/index.html\\\">PDSA</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n <p>\r\n Sunday  2/6/2007 \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n Lucky Frog spawn. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n <p>\r\n Friday 2/3/2007 \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n Frog spawn laid. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Friday 15/12/2006\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n Heard a report of someone having seen a Speckled Wood Buttterfly in Stourbridge this week. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Monday 13/11/2006\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n 20 Kg of bulbs planted in church grounds. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Monday 6/11/2006\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n Might be worth buying a pair of binoculars.\r\n <br />\r\n If only to locate the Raspberries\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Sunday November 5th  \r\n<p>\r\n Raspberry season continues.     \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Thursday November 2nd  \r\n<p>\r\n Buzzard seen flying at treetop height around church.     \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Sunday  October  8th  \r\n<p>\r\n Warm weather brings a late crop of raspberries.     \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR />\r\n<p>\r\n Monday October  2nd  \r\n<p>\r\n Plague of slugs.    </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR />\r\n<p>\r\n Thursday September 20th  \r\n<p>\r\n An unseasonably hot sticky day. Temperature 26C?  Tulip tree looking very unhappy, dropping brown crinkly leaves everywhere.    </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Tuesday September 4th 4.00am \r\n<p>\r\nVery loud Owl heard hooting in church park.    </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Tuesday July 24th\r\n<p>\r\nIntensive watering of the Tulip tree (a bucket or two of grey water every day) seems to have made a differance. No sign of brown leaves.  </p>\r\n  \r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Thursday July 13th\r\n <p>\r\n  The Tulip tree, planted last year is dropping lots of brown leaves probably due to lack of rain.     </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Wednesday July 12th\r\n <p>\r\n  Late night rustling sound in bushes turns out to be a hedgehog.   </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Monday July  3rd\r\n <p>\r\n  Kestral circling high over new park.    </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Tuesday  June 28th\r\n <p>\r\n  10.00pm  What looked like a slow moving plastic bag turned out to be a hedgehog on the church drive.   </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Wednesday June 21st\r\n <p>\r\n  Pair of twig like legs sticking out of Blackbirds nest.  Looks like another bird is dead. Good news the other baby was out and about. Looking a bit lost, and still being fed by its parents.   </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Saturday 17th June\r\n <p>\r\n  Heard today of tragic end to last years Coal Tits. \r\n  Unable to escape and died in situ.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Friday 16th June \r\n <p>\r\n  Big fat ugly magpie prowling near Blackbird nest.\r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Wednesday 14th June \r\n <p>\r\n  Blackbird young found dead on drive. Did it fall or was it kicked?   \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Monday 12th June \r\n <p>\r\n  Owl heard hooting very clearly at quarter past midnight. \r\n  Noise coming from new park. Despite looking intently at some very dark trees \r\n  I failed to see the bird.  \r\n </p>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Wednesday June 7th\r\n <p>\r\n  Blackbirds nesting in church hedge. \r\n  Young barely audible above noise of traffic and men demolishiing fence post. \r\n </p>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Friday  May 26th\r\n <p>\r\n Coal Tits nesting inside window guards of East Window.  \r\n Can\\\'t see how the young     get in or out. The parents feed them through \r\n the grill. \r\n </p>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Monday May 22nd\r\n <p>\r\n  Owl heard hooting in the trees of the new park.  Is it a Tawny Owl?  \r\n </p>\r\n</P>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2007-06-25'),(32,'MENU_ITEM',400,1500,'NO','Christianity Explored','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nChristianity Explored\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> \r\nA chance to get to grips with the basics of the Christian Faith. Look at Mark’s Gospel to understand and gain insight into life’s big questions:\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhat is God like? \r\n<br />\r\nWho is Jesus? \r\n<br />\r\nWhy am I here?\r\n<br />\r\nWhere am I going? \r\n<br />\r\nWhat happens when I die?\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nStarts on Tuesday 24th April at 10.30 am—12.00 noon meeting in the Net Café. It is hoped that after the Course the group will run on and become a permanent House/Growth Group. If interested see Simon Falshaw or Trica Hall-Wood for more details. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Suitable if you want to find out about Christianity and Jesus from scratch or are returning to a faith than has gone cold.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n <p>\r\n Developed over 10 years, \r\n <a href=\"http://www.christianityexplored.com/\">Christianity Explored</a>\r\n is an informal course for people who\'d like to investigate Christianity, \r\n or just brush up on the basics. \r\n </p>\r\n\r\n <p>\r\n It explores who Jesus was, what his aims were, \r\n and what it means to follow him.\r\n </p>\r\n	\r\n <p>\r\n You\'re not asked to pray, sing, or read aloud, \r\n and you can ask any question you like.\r\n  Or, if you prefer, you can come along and simply listen.\r\n </p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Contact\r\n <br />\r\n\r\n Simon Falshaw\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"simon.falshaw@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n <br />\r\n\r\n Or\r\n <br />\r\n\r\n Office\r\n\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"office@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Telephone 01384-423142 or 01384-894948\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=dispforthevent.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"forthcomingeventsearch\" \r\nvalue=\"Christianity Explored\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"View Course Schedule\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2012-04-02'),(61,'MENU_ITEM',500,200,'YES','Net Cafe','','<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\n  Net Cafe \r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe Net Cafe is a place for the community to come and enjoy a warm and welcoming atmosphere and somewhere to bring or meet new friends. You can just use the Net Cafe to browse the web, send or receive e-mails, work or shop.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"slideshow\" style=\"float:left; padding:1em;\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"active\">\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/netcafe/netcafe003.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 5\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/netcafe/netcafe004.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 6\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/netcafe/netcafe006.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 2\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n   