e Partnership\r\n</h4>\r\n \r\n<p>\r\nResidents in the Lye and Wollescote Partnership area can decide actions about issues affecting their area.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe Lye and Wollescote Partnership works to promote neighbourhood and social renewal in the Lye, Wollescote and Pedmore Fields area.\r\nPACT is open to all residents, business owners and local and community voluntary groups living or working within the Lye and Wollescote and Pedmore Fields area who are interested in regeneration.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt is supported by the neighbourhood management team and other council representatives. This gives communities the opportunity to influence the actions of service providers and discuss issues needing action. Other partners include local councillors, schools, police, faith organisations, connexions and representatives from Dudley Council\\\'s libraries, housing and education teams.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe group will receive regular reports from Lye youth PACT (Partners and Communities Together) which aims to identify and address issues of community safety and well-being in the area. Lye\\\'s youth PACT is among the first of its kind in the country.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe youth PACT is made up of eight young people aged between 14 and 17 from the Lye and Claycroft Place area. The group came together to work to combat the local negative perception of young people in the area. They\\\'ve been so successful that youth issues are no longer identified as a priority issue at Lye PACT meetings. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLocal Contacts\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n  <li>\r\n  Keith Stroyde (Youth and Community Worker) \r\n  <br />\r\n  Office 01384 - 894948\r\n  <br />\r\n  Mobile 07811 - 343213\r\n  <br />\r\n\r\n<form action=\\\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\\\" method=\\\"post\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"hidden\\\" name=\\\"emailrecipient\\\" \r\nvalue=\\\"keithstroyde@hotmail.co.uk\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"Email\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n  </li>\r\n \r\n  <li>\r\n  Tremaine (Neighbourhood Management) 01384 - 812357\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <li>\r\n  Kat (Young Persons, Community Safety, Co-ordinator) 01384 - 813278 \r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>\r\n  PCSO Stuart Preece (Lye Police) 0121 - 626 - 8059\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>\r\n  PCSO Sukesh Chohan (Lye Police) 0121 - 626 - 8059\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n','LEFT','2012-02-20'),(58,'MENU_ITEM',400,1000,'NO','Mum\'s Prayer Support Group','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nMum\'s Prayer Support Group\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMeets every Tuesday 10:00 am - 1:00 pm\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Contact\r\n  <br />\r\n  <br />\r\n  Sue Falshaw 01384 - 423142\r\n  <br />\r\n\r\n  Sue Falshaw\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"sue.falshaw@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n','LEFT','2009-09-21'),(59,'MENU_ITEM',400,1400,'NO','The Alpha Course','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nThe Alpha Course\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe course is based around small groups of about 12 people, hosted by one or two leaders whose role is to facilitate and encourage discussion.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nCourses vary in size, from one small group meeting in a home, to hundreds of people in a larger venue. Some courses are held over morning coffee or during a lunch hour, most are evening courses, typically lasting 2 hours. Whatever the course size, people tend to remain in the same small groups for the duration of the course so they can get to know each other, continue discussions and deepen friendships.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe whole course usually lasts for 10 weeks, with a day or weekend away in the middle.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEach session begins with a meal or refreshments - a chance to get to know others in the small group. There is then a short talk, which looks at a different aspect of the Christian faith each week.This is followed by a time of discussion in the small groups, where everyone is welcome to contribute their opinion, ask questions and discuss with the rest of the group.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe emphasis is upon exploration and discovery in a relaxed and informal environment.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nPress Comments:\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\n<i>\r\nWhat distinguishes Alpha from other initiatives is the easy-going, relaxed feel of the proceedings - that, and its astonishing success.\r\n<br />\r\nTimes\r\n</i>\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\n<i>\r\nAlpha is an unqualified triumph.\r\n<br />\r\nDaily Telegraph\r\n</i>\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\n<i>\r\nWhat Alpha offers and what is attracting thousands of people is \r\npermission, rare in secular culture, to discuss the big questions - \r\nlife and death and their meaning.\r\n<br />\r\nGuardian\r\n</i>\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nOther\r\n<a href=\\\"http://uk.alpha.org/press\\\">Press Articles</a>\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n Contact\r\n <br />\r\n\r\n Simon Falshaw\r\n<form action=\\\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\\\" method=\\\"post\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"hidden\\\" name=\\\"emailrecipient\\\" \r\nvalue=\\\"simon.falshaw@christchurchlye.org.uk\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"Email\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n\r\n Or\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n Office\r\n\r\n<form action=\\\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\\\" method=\\\"post\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"hidden\\\" name=\\\"emailrecipient\\\" \r\nvalue=\\\"office@christchurchlye.org.uk\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"Email\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Telephone 01384-423142 or 01384-894948\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<form action=\\\"index.php?displaypage=dispforthevent.php\\\" method=\\\"post\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"hidden\\\" name=\\\"forthcomingeventsearch\\\" \r\nvalue=\\\"Alpha\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"View Course Schedule\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2011-09-09'),(65