lass=\"active\">\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw001.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 1\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw002.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 2\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw003.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 3\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw004.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw005.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 5 />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw006.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 6\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw007.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 7\" />\r\n    </div>    \r\n<!--\r\nUnknown problem with this one\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw008.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 8\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n-->\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw009.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 9\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/straw/straw010.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 10\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Thanks to all who came along.</b>\r\n</p>','LEFT','2009-07-11'),(106,'MENU_ITEM',500,1200,'NO','Youth Link','http://www.myspace.com/keithatlye','','LEFT','2011-05-09'),(107,'MENU_ITEM',400,600,'YES','Forthcoming Events','dispforthevent.php','','LEFT','2012-05-31'),(108,'MENU_ITEM',400,1300,'NO','August Summer Barbeque','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nAugust Summer Barbeque\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nPictures of the Barbeque that took place on Friday 7th August 2009.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"float:left;\">\r\n\r\n<div id=\"slideshow\" style=\"padding-left:1em; padding-bottom:1em;\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"active\">\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq001.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 1\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq002.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 2\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq003.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 3\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq004.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq005.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 5\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/churchwalk/cwalk006.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 6\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq007.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 7\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq008.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 8\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq009.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 9\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/bbq/bbq010.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 10\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Thanks to all who came along.</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','LEFT','2009-08-12'),(109,'MENU_ITEM',450,1100,'YES','Church Bells Restoration Project','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Church Bells Restoration Project</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nThe unique church bells of Christ Church, Lye, Stourbridge. One of the lightest peals in the UK and the only ones cast in Belgium.\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nLatest News - 22nd of April 2012\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nThanks to David Chiswell for a detailed progress report and history of the restoration project so far. David\'s remarks are given below:\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe local ringing\r\nassociation have for many years been pestering the previous and\r\npresent vicar to get some remedial work done on the bells before they\r\nbecame unsafe. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDuring one of his inspections the church architect\r\nnoticed that the steel beams supporting the bell frame\r\nwere extensively corroded. The DAC bells adviser was asked to inspect\r\nthe bells who unsurprisingly reported  exactly what David and myself\r\nhad been saying for years - that the bells were becoming unsafe \r\nand remedial if not restoration work\r\nshould be done as soon as possible.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n That, briefly summarises how the\r\nrestoration poject came into being. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe \r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wdcra.org.uk/\">\r\nWorcestershire & Districts Change Ringing Association\r\n</a>\r\nW&DCRA \r\nruns a Belfry\r\nAdvisory Panel (BAP) of which I am a member. As such we give help and advise in\r\nall matters concerning bells. My involvement with the committee come\r\nabout because I have over fifty years ringing experience, I am a time\r\nserved maintenance engineer who has been involved with bell\r\nmaintenance for almost the same number of years. \r\n</p<\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe present Vicar (Simon Falshaw) asked if David and I would be prepared to sit on a\r\ncommittee set up to raise the money required, get quotes from suitable\r\ncompanies. This we have done.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWith quotes coming in\r\nat 30 to 35 thousand pounds, any savings that could be made were. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe one big\r\nsaving was to do work that did not require the expertise of the bell\r\nhanger, that is removing the bells, cleaning the frame, replacing the steel\r\ngrillage under the bell frame and of course helping to put the bells\r\nback in. That basically is what I have agreed to do with the help of\r\nmy colleagues from the BAP. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThat in a nutshell is what is happening to\r\nget the bells back into working order.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTo date the following has happened.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\nAlong with my colleagues we removed the bells\r\nready for collection by the restorer. \r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\nThe \r\n<a href=\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=church002.php#church_bells\">\r\nbells have been taken out\r\n</a>\r\nand sent to \r\n<a href=\"http://www.bellhangers.com/\">\r\nMatthew Higby\r\n</a> who are the best bell hangers of small bells. He is\r\ncurrently making new wheels, clappers, headstocks etc for the bells to\r\nbe rehung on and replacing all the old fittings with new up to date and\r\nmore suitable fittings.\r\n</li> \r\n\r\n<li>\r\nWe have also lifted the bell frame from the steel grillage\r\non one side, removed the old steel beams on that side and replaced\r\nthem with new beams that have been galvanised to help stop them from\r\nrusting. \r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\nWe have now lifted the frame on the other side, removed the\r\nremaining beam and will shortly be inserting the replacement beam.\r\nWhen this is done the frame will be put back into position and\r\nfastened back down to the new steel grillage. New stainless steel tie\r\nbars will be made to replace the ones that are badly corroded ie all\r\n14 of them. The frame has to be cleaned and wood preservative applied\r\nto it.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThat should have been the end of my involvement but when we\r\nwere making a opening in the ceiling to get the bells out we found\r\nthat the ceiling was made out of totally unsuitable material, what was\r\nholding it up was bits of 2x2 nailed to timbers of a dubious quality.\r\nThese timbers are also the floor joists to the belfry floor. We are\r\nnow awaiting the outcome of a faculty application to replace both the\r\nfloor joists and the ceiling.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\" http://www.expressandstar.com/news/2012/02/03/church-bells-ring-the-changes-after-120-years/\">\r\nExpress and Star\r\n</a>\r\nnewspaper piece of Friday 3rd February 2012\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nPictures of the Bells being removed for their restoration may\r\nbe found in the\r\n<a href=\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=church002.php#church_bells\">\r\nImage Gallery.\r\n</a>\r\n\r\nMany thanks to \r\n<a href=\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=13\">\r\nKeith Stroyde\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n for having the presence of mind to whip his phone out and take the pictures.\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe \r\n<a href=\"http://www.wdcra.org.uk/\">\r\nWorcestershire & Districts\r\nChange Ringing Association\r\n</a>\r\n \r\nwebsite is useful for more detailed information regarding Church Bells.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>History of the Bells</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nMr. Owen Freeman a public spirited gentleman who served on the Burial Board, was on the the Board of Orchard Lane school and a Committee member of Lye Institute. He was manager of George King-Harrison\'s brick works in Dudley Road which became the site of Folkes Forge and now Folkes Trading Estate.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHe was responsible for the original installation of the Bells which were manufactured by and purchased from \r\n<a href=\"http://www.gcna.org/data/IXfoundryVanaerschodt.html\">\r\nSeverin Van Aerschodt\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n of\r\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leuven#History\">\r\nLeuven\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n\r\nBelgium\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe eight bells are amongst the lightest in the world as far as Church or Tower Bells are concerned, therefore of great historical value and should be cherished and preserved.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe largest Bell weighs 3.5cwt (180Kgs), the smallest ways 0.75cwt (35Kgs). \r\nEach of the bells is named after a Christian virtue.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>\r\nFaith, Hope, Patience, Love, Wisdom, Truth, Joy and Peace.\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"slideshow\" style=\"float:left; padding:1em;\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"active\">\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/bells/bells001.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 1\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/bells/bells002.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 2\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/bells/bells003.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 3\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/bells/bells004.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/bells/bells005.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/bells/bells006.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Why do we need the Bells</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nChange ringing in the present form is an ancient art which has been carried out for about 400 hears but bells have called the faithful to worship for many years before that.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nBells aid us in our worship of God. They call us to services. They peal joyfully on wedding days and on the great feast days of the Church.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThey toll mournfully as the departed receive the Church\'s last blessing.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe sweet voices of the Bells direct our hearts toward God and draw us to Church to experience the presence of Christ, to listen to the word of God and to offer our prayers.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>What needs to be done</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nThe bells have to be dismantled and transported to the bellhangers. Thet then need work done to their crowns and clappers. New headstocks have to be made and fitted. New bearings fitted to headstocks and heavy steel bedplates made. New light wheels will be manufactured from English Oak and Ash. New Ash stays and clappers fitted.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThey would then possibly be cleaned and tuned to further improve their tone.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe bells would then be transported back to the Church and with the help of volunteers hoisted into the tower and hung on new bedplates.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>This work will cost in the region of 40,000 gbp</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>How you may help</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nThere are different ways that you can help the Restoration Appeal. If you have any ideas for helping us to raise funds then please contact the Church Office.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDonation Forms \r\n<a href=\"bells/bellsdonate001.pdf\">pdf</a>\r\n<a href=\"bells/bellsdonate001.doc\">MS Word</a>\r\n<a href=\"bells/bellsdonate001.txt\">ASCII Text</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nRestoration Committee Chairman Mr. Robert Field 01384 - 894657\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nChurch Office  01384 - 894948\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"office@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email Church Office\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<object width=\"480\" height=\"385\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/9A-3gKyi1Ok&hl=en_GB&fs=1\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/9A-3gKyi1Ok&hl=en_GB&fs=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"480\" height=\"385\"></embed></object>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<object width=\"480\" height=\"385\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/KFbujZTk4fo&hl=en_GB&fs=1\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/KFbujZTk4fo&hl=en_GB&fs=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"480\" height=\"385\"></embed></object>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','RIGHT','2012-04-22'),(111,'MENU_ITEM',1100,100,'NO','Wasted Bandwidth','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Wasted Bandwidth</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nGlance at the bottom left hand corner of your browser when logging onto most commercial websites and you may be astonished to see the number of sites flickering through as you wait for the requested page to load.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis is cross site scripting whereby your browsing habits are reported to numerous websites without your knowledge or permission and advertisements are loaded from third party sites. For those with unlimited bandwidth and broadband this is merely an irritation and an invasion of privacy, for those with a fixed monthly limit on downloads and worse a dial up connection it is a severe nuisance. For those with a fixed monthly limit it may even result in increased bills.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere is a solution - Use the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.mozilla-europe.org/en/firefox\\\" >\r\nFirefox\r\n</a>\r\nbrowser coupled with two add ons. \r\n<a href=\\\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/1865\\\">\r\nAdBlocker \r\n</a>\r\n\r\nand \r\n<a href=\\\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/722\\\">\r\nNoScript\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBoth of the above Firefox addons significantly increase your security and browsing speed whilst removing unwanted advertising.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso see the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=113\\\">\r\nFlash Player Security\r\n</a>\r\npage.','RIGHT','2010-12-31'),(112,'MENU_ITEM',500,300,'YES','Relaxed Art','','<br />\r\n<h2>Relaxed Art</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMonday mornings 10-30 to 12-00 \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nRun by Naomi in a relaxed atmosphere\r\nhere at Christ Church. Come along and join with\r\nothers in exploring your talents.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"float:left; margin-left:0em; margin-top:1em; margin-right:1em;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"slideshow\" style=\"padding-left:1em; padding-bottom:1em;\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"active\">\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/relaxed-art/relaxed-art-001.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 1\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/relaxed-art/relaxed-art-002.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 2\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/relaxed-art/relaxed-art-003.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 3\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n   \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- Try this -->\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>\r\nWhy Looking at Paintings together?\r\n</h2>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt\'s about empathy. About learning to hear each others voice more and more as we explore three paintings over the course of three weeks.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMeetings on:\r\n<br/>\r\nTuesday 1st May at 7.30 pm\r\n<br/>\r\nTuesday 8th May at 7.30 pm\r\n<br />\r\nTuesday 15th May at 7.30 pm\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEach person in the group will see things differently from others. Will perhaps like or dislike certain aspects of a painting or will have a different memory or experience that might link in some way to the painting. The more I can hear others points of view, the more my own insights and understanding will grow, not only about the painting but perhaps more importantly about my fellow human beings.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nFirstly each person in the group would briefly describe their immediate impression of the painting. For instance; \"this makes me think of a hot summers day in July\". Then we would take it in turn to simply describe the bare facts. Eg: \"there is a woman wearing a blue dress\". Each person would then say something about relationships between and or objects in the painting. Eg: \"The Lighthouse looks like it is guiding two boats safely to harbour\" or \"The woman\'s cloak is floating round here and it makes me feel that a cloud has floated closer to the earth\". \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThen we would describe what the painting may remind us of in our own lives. Eg: \"I went on a boat trip...\" Also we can comment about how the painting makes us feel. Eg: \"I like the way such and such\" or \"such and such makes us feel uncomfortable\".\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAnd finally what we think/feel/imagine what the intention of the artist might have been.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe purpose of discussing a painting in this way is the opposite of presenting what we know. It is to learn about it through each others insights and imagination.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nNaomi Simone\r\n\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"naomi.simone@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email Naomi\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n','LEFT','2012-06-13'),(113,'MENU_ITEM',1100,200,'NO','Flash Player Security','','<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Flash Player Security</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAs of \r\n<b>\r\nFriday 11/6/2010 \r\n</b>\r\nAdobe have released an emergency fix for a flaw in \r\nAdobe Flash - This is the tool that a web browser uses to display sound and\r\nvideo.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe release addresses what is known is a zero day security flaw. In other words,\r\nunlike most security flaws this was discovered roaming the Internet before any\r\nopportunity was given to fix the problem. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt is rather nasty as it permits a computer running old versions of Flash to \r\nbecome part of a botnet.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<h4>\r\nUpgrade your version of \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.adobe.com/products/flashplayer/\\\" >\r\nAdobe Flash\r\n</a>\r\n to 10.1\r\n</h4>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere are some things not commonly known about the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/\\\">\r\nFlash Player</a>\r\nthat exists on virtually every PC in the world. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nFirstly, Flash runs inside a Browser as a plugin which means that although Flash content appears inside the browser (if its not run in full screen mode) it is executing as a program in its own right.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis means that Flash has access to a computer\\\'s hardware, disk drives, camera, microphone etc.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSecondly, Flash stores cookies and uses disk caches independently of the Browser in which it runs. Current versions of Flash do not respect Private Browsing sessions, any information stored by Flash during private browsing sessions is not deleted when the private browsing session is completed.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nUpdate 12/6/10\r\n</b>\r\n - release 10.1 of Flash claims to recognize private browsing \r\nsessions for most modern major browsers - Firefox, IE8, Safari etc.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWorse, these Flash cookies may be massively larger than normal browser cookies and they are never deleted.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMore information about  \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.adobe.com/devnet/flashplayer/articles/privacy_mode_fp10.1.html\\\">\r\nPrivate Browsing in Flash Player\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt is possible to turn on a computers camera and microphone from Flash. This isn\\\'t a bug or a security exploit its a deliberate feature built into Flash. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt is possible to change Flash\\\'s settings either by right clicking on a playing Flash item or by visiting the \r\n\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.macromedia.com/support/documentation/en/flashplayer/help/settings_manager.html\\\">\r\nSettings Manager.\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIts well worth a look - it is rather suprising what Flash can get up to on a computer without the users knowlege.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nFor the Firefox user there is the \r\n<a href=\\\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/6623\\\"\r\n>\r\nBetter Privacy\r\n</a>\r\naddon that cleans up Flash Cookies - Flash calls these cookies Local Shared Objects (LSOs). \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAlso see the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=111\\\">\r\nWasted Bandwidth\r\n</a>\r\npage.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b> \r\nUpdate 27/06/1010\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nThe latest release of the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/\\\">\r\nFlash Player</a>\r\n fixes some security holes.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n','RIGHT','2010-12-31'),(114,'MENU_ITEM',400,400,'NO','Easter Services','','<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Easter Services</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>\r\nWednesday April  4th    3-30 - 6-00 pm\r\n</h2>\r\n<b>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.messychurch.org.uk/\">\r\nMessy Church \r\n</a>\r\nEaster \r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nFor children and parents/carers together. Fun with lots of craft activities, followed by a short time of worship focused around Easter and then food. Cost Children 50p adults £1\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>\r\nThursday April 5th  7 pm  \r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<b>\r\nMaundy Thursday Commununion \r\n</b>\r\n <br />\r\nA simple meal leading into communion followed by a time of quite reflection thinking about the Last Supper and Jesus\' arrest in the garden  of Gethsemane.  Stay for as long or as little time as you like.   \r\nCost Adults £1-50  Children 50p. Please sign the list in church if you are coming. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nGood Friday - April 6th\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nCross Making 10-30 am\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nWe will be making crosses out of rubbish to remind us of how Jesus carried our spiritual rubbish (ie our sins)  on himself on the cross. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nWalk and worship  11-30 am \r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nWe walk up to Wollescote Park together with all the churches in Lye carrying our crosses for a short service at 12-00 noon.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nQuiet around the cross 1-00 - 3-00pm\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nWe sit in silence with occasional readings from Luke\'s account of the crucifixtion.  An opporutunity to think deeply about the meaning of Jesus\' dying on the cross.  \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>\r\nEaster Sunday Sunday April  8th\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n9-00 am Holy Communion\r\n<br />\r\n10-45 am All Age Worship  - followed by short service of communion\r\n<br />\r\n6-30 pm Easter Praise \r\n</p> \r\n\r\n \r\n','LEFT','2012-04-09'),(115,'MENU_ITEM',300,200,'NO','The Westminster Declaration','','<br />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDear All,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI suspect that like me you often feel as a mainstream Christian \r\na sense of marginalisation from our political parties and the \r\ngeneral direction of society.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe \r\n \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.westminster2010.org.uk\\\">\r\nWestminster Declaration\r\n</a>\r\n\r\ncalls on all political parties to respect Christian freedom of conscience. This petition, launched by Lord Carey and others at Easter already has 40,000 signatures despite being largely ignored by the media. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI think signing it is a very positive way of making a difference. Please sign and forward it.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSimon Falshaw\r\n\r\n<form action=\\\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\\\" method=\\\"post\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"hidden\\\" name=\\\"emailrecipient\\\" \r\nvalue=\\\"simon.falshaw@christchurchlye.org.uk\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"Email Simon\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2010-05-12'),(116,'MENU_TITLE',300,100,'NO','General Election 2010','','','LEFT','2010-05-12'),(117,'MENU_ITEM',300,400,'NO','Voting with Amos','','&#65279;\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Voting with Amos X</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAs the National and Local elections approach, we offer the following list of questions you may wish to use as a \\\"checklist\\\" to help you decide how to cast your vote. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe main, numbered questions are the headings of the talk given by Graham Dyer to the morning congregations of Christ Church on 11th April 2010, based on the message of the Book of Amos in the Old Testament.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nHow well-off is our country actually?\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nWhat are the responsibilities which come with privilege? (Chs.1, 2 & 3)\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nWhat\\\'s creeping in to our society? \r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nAre any issues or policies ungodly? (Chs.4 & 5)\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nAre we being complacent about things?\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nHow should we challenge ungodly issues and policies? (Ch.6)\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nWhat damage could changes cause?\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nWhat could the consequences be?  (Ch.7 1-9)\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nIs personality or spin involved?\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nBe alert to the use of character assassinations and exaggerations\r\nin campaigning. (Ch.7 10-17)\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nWhat should be the fruits of the Kingdom?\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nWhat kind of world would God want us to build for ourselves? (Chs.8 & 9)\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<b>\r\nShould we vote in our own interests, or for justice for others?\r\n</b>\r\n<br />\r\nDoes exercising our democratic right necessarily mean being self-centred?\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nWhere will you place your Cross?\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n(Adapted from \\\'The Bible Application Handbook\\\' by J I Packer & D Williams, 1999)\r\n<br />\r\nSubmitted by Rev Dr Chris Kent\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<form action=\\\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\\\" method=\\\"post\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"hidden\\\" name=\\\"emailrecipient\\\" \r\nvalue=\\\"chris.kent@christchurchlye.org.uk\\\">\r\n<input type=\\\"submit\\\" value=\\\"Email Chris\\\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2010-05-12'),(118,'MENU_ITEM',300,500,'NO','Bible and Government','http://christchurchlye.org.uk/talkbibleandgovernment.php','','LEFT','2010-05-12'),(119,'MENU_ITEM',450,600,'YES','Special Needs and Access','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nSpecial Needs and Access\r\n</h2>\r\n	\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA wheelchair ramp provides access to all ground floor areas of the Church. Toilet facilities for those with special needs are also available. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA Hearing aid loop facility is provided.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\nLarge print Hymn books are available.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nModern web browsers are able to increase the size of text for anyone who experiences difficulty viewing the website. Consult the browser documentation. Options to increase/decrease text size are normally found on the Browsers View menu.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\\\"http://christchurchlye.org.uk/googlemaps.php\\\">\r\nHow to find us\r\n</a>\r\n<br />\r\nPublic Transport Information - \r\n<a \r\nhref=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=120\\\">\r\nBus and Rail\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n','RIGHT','2012-02-24'),(120,'MENU_ITEM',450,500,'YES','Public Transport ','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Public Transport</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Bus</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere are three bus stops within 100 yards of the church.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe 276 Dudley - Stourbridge and 9 Birmingham - Stourbridge Services stop directly outside the Church.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\nTraveline Journey\r\n<a \r\nhref=\\\"http://www.travelinemidlands.co.uk/JourneyPlanner.jsp?vm_Reset_str=true\\\">\r\nPlanner\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Rail</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLye Railway Station is within 400 yards of the church and is marked on this\r\n<a href=\\\"http://christchurchlye.org.uk/googlemaps.php\\\">map</a>\r\n<br />\r\nInformation about the \r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.nationalrail.co.uk/stations/lye/details.html\\\">Station</a>\r\n<br />\r\nNational Rail Enquiries Journey  \r\n<a href=\\\"http://ojp.nationalrail.co.uk/en/s/planjourney/query\\\">Planner</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\\\"http://christchurchlye.org.uk/googlemaps.php\\\">\r\nHow to find us\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n','RIGHT','2012-03-05'),(122,'MENU_TITLE',1500,100,'NO','Site Services','','<br />\r\n<h1>Site Services</h1>','RIGHT','2012-06-12'),(124,'MENU_ITEM',600,100,'YES','Lye Library','','<br />\r\n<h2>\r\n<b>\r\nLye Library\r\n</b>\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA superb local institution which has just undergone a massive refit with new computers.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.dudley.gov.uk/leisure-and-culture/libraries/find-a-library/lye-library-/\">\r\nLye Library \r\n</a>\r\n\r\nis an exceptional operation, the staff \r\nare most helpful, friendly  and work very hard to provide many resources, in particular they offer child reading clubs in a relaxed way.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere is an active Job Club.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDaily newspapers including foreign language newspapers are freely available.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nIf you unable to visit the Library please look in at the \r\n<a href=\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=61\">\r\nNet Cafe\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTry the \r\n<a href=\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=3\">\r\nLion and Toddler Group\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease visit the Library, the more people who visit makes it less easier to close.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2012-04-06'),(125,'MENU_ITEM',500,800,'YES','Scouts, Cubs and Beavers','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Scouts Cubs and Beavers</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://scouts.org.uk/\">The Scout Association website</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Scouts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://scouts.org.uk/\">Scouts website</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://stourbridgescouts.org/\">Stourbridge Scout Association</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Cubs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://scouts.org.uk/cubs/\">Cubs Website</a> 8 - 10 and a half\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Beavers</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://scouts.org.uk/beavers/\">Beavers Website</a> 6 - 8 years\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2012-05-05');
